Pfizer's stock surges toward biggest post-earnings gain in over 9 years


Shares of Pfizer Inc. PFE, -0.63% surged 4.6% in afternoon trading Tuesday, to pace the Dow Jones Industrial Average's PFE, -0.63% gainers, after the drug maker reported second-quarter results that beat expectations and raised its financial guidance. The stock is currently on track to post the best one-day post-earnings gain since it shot up 5.5% on Feb. 1, 2011, after Pfizer reported fourth-quarter 2010 results. On the day of the past 20 quarterly reports, Pfizer's stock has gained eight times, with an average gain of 2.8%, according to an analysis of FactSet data. After the other 12 earnings reports, the average decline was 1.9%.